Join Our Team A dedicated group of individuals–our staff, board of trustees, interns, and volunteers–make this museum a leading cultural institution and community pillar. As active stewards and educators of history and culture, of our historic site, and of our collections, we strive to inspire an ever-growing audience to experience the local, regional, and global stories of Maine. Willock John Zittel Volunteer with Us A SENSE OF ACCOMPLISHMENT… As a nonprofit organization, the museum depends on its volunteers who annually contribute over $500,000 worth of their time, skills, and talents. As a Maine Maritime Museum volunteer, you will be able to work with others who share your interests and experience the sense of camaraderie that has lured people to the museum for over 50 years. There is something for everyone: maritime history, historic homes, gardening, art, education, and much more! Throughout the year, volunteers are invited to join in receptions, dinners, and cruises that celebrate their contributions. Volunteers who donate at least 15 hours of their time are also eligible for a complimentary membership and other exclusive benefits. VOLUNTEER LOG IN Looking for something else? To schedule a school visit for children, email us at education@maritimeme.org . To schedule a group tour for adults, email us at reservations@maritimeme.org . For weddings and private events, email us at events@maritimeme.org . For press inquiries, or anything else, email us at info@maritimeme.org . Prospective vendors for our museum store, email our store buyer at buyer@maritimeme.org . To inquire about donating an item to the collection, please complete this form . Have a question for the Curatorial Team? Submit a research request . Subscribe to Our Newsletter Sign up with your email address to receive news and updates. Email Address Sign Up Thank you! Palm Tree Club Miami 1819 79th Street Causeway North Bay Village, FL 33141 Hotel Phone: 305-865-7100 Front Desk Inquiries: reception@palmtreeclubmiami.com Reservations: r eservations@palmtreeclubmiami.com Restaurant Phone: 786-204-1366 Email: dining@palmtreeclubmiami.com Marina Email: boats@palmtreeclubmiami.com Radio Channel: #71 Live Events Email: VIP@palmtreeclubmiami.com Thank you for reaching out! We will be in touch shortly. First Name * Last Name * Email Address * Comments Privacy Policy agreement I have read and agree to the Privacy Policy . Yes, I would like to receive emails with exclusive specials and offers. Submit FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS Live Music & Events What time does the live music start? Doors open at 3 PM. Is there a cover charge for guests to enjoy the live music? Only for ticketed events. Get your tickets on Posh: https://posh.vip/g/ptc-miami . Do I need a reservation to see the live music? Not unless it's a ticketed event. How long does the live music performance last? Sunset parties typically go until 12 AM. Is the music indoors or outdoors? Both. Do you have a schedule or calendar for upcoming live music performances? Yes! Be sure to check our socials and website for more details: www.palmtreeclubmiami.com . Do you offer special deals or promotions? For offers and experiences, check our OpenTable: Palm Tree Club Miami Restaurant - North Bay Village, FL | OpenTable . Are there specific days or nights dedicated to live music? Typically Saturdays and Sundays, but please check our website for more details! What time will the DJs perform at the events we've published? Stay tuned to our social media for updates on set times. What’s the dress code for events? Come as you are—sneakers, flip-flops, heels, sequins, or bikini tops. Feel free to wear jeans, shorts, or even your suit (but we hope you lose the tie). Hotel General Information Is there a minimum age to check in? Yes, guests must be 21 years or older to check-in and will be required to present a valid photo ID, in addition to their method of payment. What time is check-in and check-out? Check-in time: 4pm Check-out time: 11am Can I check in early or check out late? Early check-in or late check-out may be available upon request, subject to availability. Please contact the front desk for more information. How late can I check-in? Our front desk is available 24 hours. What is required to check-in? Guests must be 21 years or older to check in and will be required to present a valid photo ID in addition to their method of payment. Is parking available at the hotel? Yes, complimentary on-site parking is available for all hotel guests. Can I store my luggage before or after I check out? Yes, complimentary luggage storage is available at our Front Desk. Is the hotel accessible for guests with disabilities? Yes, we have accessible rooms, ramps, and elevators for your convenience. Please inform us of any specific needs prior to your arrival. Are there any extra charges or resort fees? $20 plus taxes Resort Fee is applied to all reservations. Is the hotel pet-friendly? Yes. A non-refundable $100 pet fee applies. Room and Facilities Do the rooms include complimentary Wi-Fi? Yes, free Wi-Fi is available in all rooms and public areas of the hotel. When will my room be cleaned, and how do I request additional items? Your room will receive full cleaning service every third day of your stay. For any requests, such as extra towels or amenity refills, please contact the Front Desk at any time. Are there any amenities in the rooms? Our rooms come with air conditioning, a flat-screen TV, minibar, safe, Bluetooth speaker, hair dryer, and ironing board. Check the room description for specific details. Do you have accessible rooms? We offer three accessible room types - our Accessible Classic King and Accessible Classic Double, Accessible Deluxe King. For more specifics, check out our Accessibility page. Is there a smoking policy in the hotel? Our hotel is smoke-free, and smoking is only allowed in designated areas. Please ensure compliance with our smoking policy. A $250 cleaning fee will be applied if any odor is found in the room. Do you offer breakfast? Brunch begins at 11am. Do you have a restaurant or bar on-site? Yes, we have Palm Tree Club Miami Restaurant. Open daily, our restaurant serves up coastal-American food in a casual dining environment, with all your favorites & Miami’s best sunset views! Do you offer laundry and dry cleaning services? Yes, laundry and dry cleaning services are available. Booking and Payments Does the hotel accept traveler’s checks as payment? No, we do not accept traveler’s checks as payment. Does the hotel require any deposit at check in? Yes, at check-in, we require a $150 incidental deposit per stay, in addition to the room and tax charges. This is just a hold on the credit card. If the guest doesn’t incur any incidentals or make any purchases during their stay, the hold will be released within 5 to 7 business days after check-out. Does the hotel require any deposit prior to checking in? Pre-stay deposits are dependent upon the rate plan reserved. What type of credit cards are accepted at the hotel? MasterCard, Visa, American Express, and Discover are all accepted. What is your cancellation policy? Cancellation policy depends on the reservation rate booked. We offer rates with a refundable reservation up to 72 hours before arrival, as well as discounted non-refundable rates. Can I book directly on your website? Yes, we recommend booking directly through our website for the best rates and special offers. Can I modify or cancel my reservation after booking? Cancellation/Modification policy depends on the reservation rate booked. We offer rates that may be cancelled or modified up to 72 hours before arrival, as well as discounted non-refundable rates that do not allow cancellations or modifications. Special Requests and Policies Can I send a package to the hotel? Yes, we’re happy to accept packages prior to your arrival. Please be sure that the name of the registered guest is included in the delivery information and be sure to use our Security/Receiving address: 1819 79th Street Causeway North Bay Village, FL 33141 Can I request special accommodations or amenities (e.g., flowers, champagne, etc.)? Yes, we can arrange special requests for a fee. Please contact us ahead of time to ensure availability. Do you offer shuttle service to the airport? We do not offer this service directly, however, our concierge services may assist in making a shuttle reservation with a 3rd party company. Additional Services Can I book tours or activities through the hotel? Yes, we’d be happy to assist with booking. Please stop by the front desk to inquire about available options. Our concierge team can also help with making reservations. Do you have a gym or fitness center? Yes, we have a brand-new fitness center, and it’s open 24 hours a day for your convenience! Reservations & Ticketing How can I contact the restaurant if I have further questions? You can reach us at 786-204-1366 or email us at dining@palmtreeclubmiami.com . Will there be commissions for promoters who refer clients? For more information, email VIP@palmtreeclubmiami.com . Contact Information How can I contact the hotel if I have further questions? You can reach us at 305-865-7100 or email us at reception@palmtreeclubmiami.com . Our team is available 24/7 to assist you. Join the Crew Thank you for your interest. Community Portal It is now easier than ever for Bunbury residents to request a service or report an issue to the City of Bunbury, through our new Community Portal. The online hub allows residents to lodge and track reports and service requests, such as reporting graffiti, litter and fallen trees or requesting bin replacements, just to name a few. Community members can sign up and create an account to stay up to date with a report or service request lodged with the City. The portal also features an AI assistant to ask questions and, where possible, get real-time information and responses. Visit the Community Portal via the button below.
